<item>
            <title>[LU-12342] lsvcgss config file overwritten on update</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12342</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The file /etc/sysconfig/lsvcgss is overwritten on rpm package upgrades as it is not marked as a configuration file, unlike /etc/request-key.d/lgssc.conf.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If the user has set options in the file, e.g. LSVCGSSDARGS=&apos;-s -m&apos; on MDS or LSVCGSSDARGS=&apos;-s -o&apos; on the OSS, they are removed and the targets will fail to mount.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Centos 7.6</environment>
        <key id="55757">LU-12342</key>
